The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 2: The Mahindra group today restructured its infrastructure development sector into two divisions and added new members on its executive board. The hospitality sector, comprising Mahindra Holidays amp; Resorts India and its subsidiaries, will report to Ramesh Ramanathan. The real estate sector, comprising Mahindra Lifespace Developers and Mahindra World City, will report to Anita Arjundas.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 2: The Employees Provident Fund Organsisation will be allowed to purchase long-term government bonds with a maturity of 10 years or more from the secondary market. At present, the EPFO can buy only short-term government bonds from the secondary market, except those floated by the RBI.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 2: The World Bank has committed to increase its lending to India by over three times to $7 billion in 2009-10 against the average $2.3 billion for the last four fiscals, bank president Robert Zoellick said. The banks portfolio in India consists of 68 projects with a total commitment of $19.57 billion.                            
	 Calcutta, Dec. 2: Tyre maker Dunlop India today re-opened its Shahagunj plant with 840 employees reporting for duty. However, 25 suspended workers were barred from joining.                            
	 Detroit, Dec. 2: General Motors CEO Fritz Henderson abruptly resigned on Tuesday after the companys board decided the auto maker needed to push its restructuring faster under a new leadership. GM chairman Ed Whitacre, 68, will become the interim CEO.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 2: Anil Ambanis Reliance Natural Resources Ltd has warned of higher costs and consequently higher selling price of electricity per unit in case its claim for gas at $2.34 per mBtu from RIL is turned down by the Supreme Court.                             
	 Hyderabad, Dec. 2: Wipro will hire 5,000 people in the next couple of months and is looking at recruiting graduates from non-engineering institutes.                                                                                                                          
